<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,611,667]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,323,611,635]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Remarks.</emphasis>
Of all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1870" box="[399,526,611,635]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Eryphanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[399,526,611,635]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Eryphanis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weeks" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[630,768,611,635]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Eryphanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerhardi">
<emphasis box="[630,768,611,635]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">E. gerhardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the smallest male genitalia relative to its wingspan. 
<bibRefCitation author="Casagrande, M. M." box="[192,421,643,667]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="201 - 205" refId="ref11943" refString="Casagrande, M. M. 2004. Brassolini. p. 201 - 205. In: J. B. Heppner (ed.). Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Part 4 A Checklist (ed. by G. Lamas). Association of Tropical Lepidoptera / Scientific Publishers; Gainesville. 439 p." type="book chapter" year="2004">Casagrande (2004)</bibRefCitation>
lists no subspecies for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Weeks" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[694,832,643,667]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Eryphanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gerhardi">
<emphasis box="[694,832,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">E. gerhardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
